WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.009 --> 00:00:00.870
In this scenario,

1
00:00:00.970 --> 00:00:02.769
we're working an incident which cannot be

2
00:00:02.769 --> 00:00:05.170
resolved because the root cause is unknown,

3
00:00:05.409 --> 00:00:08.479
and there is no available workaround to get the user up and running again.

4
00:00:08.760 --> 00:00:09.590
In this case,

5
00:00:09.850 --> 00:00:12.029
we will need to place the incident on hold

6
00:00:12.449 --> 00:00:15.989
and initiate the problem management process to investigate the root cause,

7
00:00:16.610 --> 00:00:18.610
identify an appropriate fix,

8
00:00:19.079 --> 00:00:22.930
or establish a viable workaround we can use to restore service temporarily.

9
00:00:24.510 --> 00:00:25.989
To place the incident on hold,

10
00:00:26.229 --> 00:00:28.100
change the state to on hold.

11
00:00:28.399 --> 00:00:29.549
When you choose this option,

12
00:00:29.790 --> 00:00:32.130
the on-hold reason field becomes available.

13
00:00:32.459 --> 00:00:33.220
From the drop-down,

14
00:00:33.509 --> 00:00:34.790
choose a waiting problem.

15
00:00:35.990 --> 00:00:36.360
OK,

16
00:00:36.439 --> 00:00:37.750
let's save our changes.

17
00:00:38.279 --> 00:00:40.380
Now we want to create a problem record to engage

18
00:00:40.380 --> 00:00:43.500
the problem management team in root cause analysis activities.

19
00:00:43.759 --> 00:00:44.349
To do this,

20
00:00:44.520 --> 00:00:47.580
open the more actions menu and choose create problem.

21
00:00:49.040 --> 00:00:50.759
A new problem record is created,

22
00:00:51.080 --> 00:00:53.700
pre-populated with data from the originating incident.

23
00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:55.319
We can make changes if we need to,

24
00:00:55.400 --> 00:00:56.099
but in this case,

25
00:00:56.439 --> 00:00:57.270
it looks good.

26
00:00:57.680 --> 00:00:59.000
So let's assign the problem.

27
00:01:00.040 --> 00:01:01.029
Click assign

28
00:01:02.830 --> 00:01:03.810
In the modal window,

29
00:01:03.939 --> 00:01:06.589
select the problem management assignment group.

30
00:01:08.949 --> 00:01:10.040
Add work notes

31
00:01:14.669 --> 00:01:15.610
Then click save.

32
00:01:16.830 --> 00:01:18.430
The problem has now been created and

33
00:01:18.430 --> 00:01:20.629
placed in the problem management group's queue,

34
00:01:20.949 --> 00:01:24.169
where it can be picked up or assigned to a problem manager for investigation.

35
00:01:25.730 --> 00:01:26.029
Now,

36
00:01:26.290 --> 00:01:27.970
if we go back to our original incident,

37
00:01:28.050 --> 00:01:28.230
you know,

38
00:01:28.290 --> 00:01:31.150
we can see the state is on hold awaiting problem.

39
00:01:31.569 --> 00:01:33.849
And if we scroll down to the related records section,

40
00:01:34.169 --> 00:01:36.269
we can see the problem record we just created

41
00:01:36.449 --> 00:01:39.889
and can quickly navigate between records as the investigation progresses.